      "message": "Skottie and (relative-sized) SVG slides now render 2x larger and get clipped out.  I\u0027m guessing it\u0027s because they use the window width/hight passed to load() \u0026 resize() to scale to full window size.\n\nAre slides supposed to compensate for the extra scale or is viewer supposed to scale down w/h before passing to slides?\n\n(ie what units are winWidth/winHeight in?)",
      "revId": "fa8b5e45028c914cf2b1b6edeff41bb960dbe8b3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
